  "text": "The RISPP architecture [CITATION_1] lies between static and dynamic approaches. Here, a set of candidate instructions are evaluated at compile time. These candidates are implemented dynamically at runtime by varying sets of so called atoms. Thus, alternative design points are chosen depending on the actual execution characteristics.",
